last_episode_to_air.name: Warrior Women of Amazonia
last_episode_to_air.overview: Josie & Gang see flashes and decide to head toward them, only to find that they were tricked into becoming slaves.

name: Josie and the Pussycats in Outer Space
original_name: Josie and the Pussycats in Outer Space
overview: Josie and the gang are accidentally launched into space.

episodes.name: Where's Josie?
episodes.overview: Finding themselves lost in space aboard a spaceship, the Pussycats land on the planetoid Zelkor and encounter a creature named Bleep. Then they find out that Josie has been kidnapped and replaced with an android!

episodes.name: Make Way for The Multi-Men
episodes.overview: The Pussycats land on a planet of cat people and soon learn from their king Kator that their queen Felina is being held prisoner. The power-mad robot Menton has a device that can create duplicates of himself or others.

episodes.name: The Sleeping Planet
episodes.overview: The Pussycats land on a planet where they expose a plot to steal a device from the Arcovians that the thief could use to rule the galaxy... if his accomplices don't double-cross him first.

episodes.name: Alien Alan
episodes.overview: The Pussycats encounter a planet where the populace depends heavily on the power of magnets. Alan is captured and brainwashed to swearing allegiance to an evil ruler.

episodes.name: The Water Planet
episodes.overview: On a water planet, the Pussycats' ship is hijacked by locals intent on conquering Earth with a water-controlling device.

episodes.name: The Sun Haters
episodes.overview: Josie and the gang encounter a race of giants allergic to the sun who steal their spaceship. The creatures have developed a fluid capable of extinguishing the Sun completely. Their leader and his henchmen plan to use the spaceship as a means of delivering the extinguisher.

episodes.name: The Mini-Man Menace
episodes.overview: The Pussycats are shanghaied by tiny robots and forced to journey to a planet ruled by an ambitious villain.

episodes.name: The Space Pirates
episodes.overview: The Pussycats' ship is seized by robot space pirates under the command of a modern-day pirate who intends to use the ship as a vessel in his pirate fleet to loot and plunder ships and planets that he comes across.

episodes.name: Anything You Can Zoo
episodes.overview: The ship containing the Pussycats lands on the planet Kalex. Josie and the gang quickly find themselves human guinea pigs with the goal of learning how earthlings will react when the frog-men attack Earth.

episodes.name: Now You See Them, Now You Don't
episodes.overview: The Pussycats encounter aliens who can seemingly become invisible at will. Josie and the others are baffled as to how to outsmart and escape the aliens, until one of them inadvertently acquires the power of invisibility.

episodes.name: The Four-eyed Dragon of Cygnon
episodes.overview: The Pussycats encounter two aliens who attempt to convince Josie and the gang into helping them against a dragon that is menacing them. Can the Pussycats figure out who is the true menace before it is too late?

episodes.name: The Forward Backward People of Xarock
episodes.overview: Josie and the gang meet a villain whose reversitron causes everything it zaps to go backwards.

episodes.name: The Hollow Planet
episodes.overview: Aliens that reside on a ship that resembles a planet plan to enslave others by using a ray that turns its victims into children.

episodes.name: All Hail Goddess Melody
episodes.overview: Melody is given a holy welcome after she is found to resemble the goddess that a planet's populace worships.

episodes.name: Outer Space Ark
episodes.overview: While Melody talks to the friendly animals on a new planetoid, Alan, Josie, and Alexandra are taken prisoner by other animals, trained for conquest.

episodes.name: Warrior Women of Amazonia
episodes.overview: Josie & Gang see flashes and decide to head toward them, only to find that they were tricked into becoming slaves.
